its an unproven legend that betsy ross made 
the nations first official flag but there was little disbelief 
among children at her house to start the celebration of the 211th 
anniversary of the flags adoption by congress 
a 22by45foot replica of the 13star flag was unfurled tuesday 
down the side of a building as 30 schoolchildren watched waving 
smaller versions of the flag 
