<TEXT>
the government has resolved a crisis 
in its relationship with nato by ruling that alliance warships will 
be allowed to visit denmark without revealing if theyre carrying 
nuclear weapons 
prime minister poul schlueter said tuesday that his government 
will notify the diplomatic missions of its nato allies of denmarks 
peacetime ban on nuclear weapons visiting vessels however will 
receive no such notice 
a dispute over toughening denmarks longstanding nuclear weapons 
ban triggered an unscheduled election may 10 that ended in a 
political stalemate and schlueter returned as prime minister in a 
minority coalition last week 
before the elections the socialist opposition pushed a 
resolution through the folketing or parliament that obliged the 
government to remind visiting warships of denmarks nuclear policy 
although the resolution of april 14 stands the new centerright 
government will send a note to the diplomatic missions of nato 
countries concerned rather than to each naval vessel schlueter 
said 
there is no mention of nuclear weapons in the note 
but the sentence the visit of the vessel is on condition that 
it takes place according regulations set down by the danish 
government will be inserted in the foreign ministrys standard 
notice 
since 1976 denmark has required all foreign warships wishing to 
pass through its waters or dock at its ports to seek permission via 
diplomatic channels 
it is the governments view that this procedure repects our 
allies policy of neither to confirm nor to deny the presence of 
nuclear weapons on board their naval vessels schlueter said 
the government has been in touch with allied governments which 
share this view he added 
the united states and britain two nuclear powers whose warships 
make frequent visits in danish ports had objected strongly to the 
resolution 
its implementation by means of a letter to naval captains could 
have prevented allied ships from participating in nato sea 
exercises in danish waters and undermine the alliances nuclear 
deterrence strategy they said 
the new cabinet the third nonsocialist administration headed 
by schlueter since 1982 was announced last friday 
svend auken leader of the main opposition social democratic 
party that sponsored the resolution called the governments move 
a weak signal to the outside world about denmarks nuclear 
policy 
