<TEXT>
up to 10 new plays by established american 
playwrights could make it to new york within the next two years 
under an ambitious plan developed by three producers and a major 
broadway theater owner 
the american playwrights project will commission works from such 
writers as christopher durang david henry hwang marsha norman 
terrence mcnally david rabe wendy wasserstein and four more 
authors to be named later 
the project financed at 200000 was announced tuesday by 
producers james b freydberg max weitzenhoffer and stephen graham 
and jujamcyn theaters which owns five broadway playhouses 
i was concerned about the fact that there were fewer american 
plays on broadway than any other season said freydberg producer 
of lanford wilsons burn this one of only six american plays 
that opened on broadway during the 198788 season 
we have formed the american playwrights project for a simple 
reason to get product he said but added that the project will 
not own an option on these works and will not influence what 
happens to them artistically 
for example there may be several readings of a play and then 
it would go to a regional theater if they were interested and from 
there the play might travel to new york said freydberg 
but there is no guarantee a show will come to broadway he 
said there is no guarantee that we would end up producing it if 
we didnt we would have a small interest in the show for the 
purpose of recouping the cost of the commission which we would 
then use to commission somebody else 
each of the playwrights will receive appromimately 15000 in 
commissions 
many of the details are still be worked out said hwang whose 
m butterfly won a tony award on sunday as best play of the 
broadway season 
i see it as an intention to work together at this point he 
said 
miss wasserstein author of the offbroadway hit isnt it 
romantic said she was approached about the project by several 
people including rocco landesman president of jujamcyn she said 
she had agreed to it although no contracts have been signed 
i always find commissions useful because they make you write 
the play she said they said we should come in and give them a 
general idea of what we are going to write but its pretty much 
anything i think thats whats appealing about it 
</TEXT>
