investigators have been unable to identify any defect common to the 
vehicles that would cause unintended acceleration 
audi has been plagued with charges that its audi 5000 sedans 
with automatic transmissions sometimes accelerate on their own 
despite several investigations the cause of the problem has never 
been pinpointed 
the center for auto safety a consumer group based in 
washington contends that at least 1646 accidents resulting in 402 
injuries and five deaths were linked to sudden acceleration when 
the car was shifted from park into gear 
