of the great lakes and the damage this was doing to buildings and 
other things along the shores 
all sorts of emergency measures were being proposed to lower the 
levels before chicago detroit and cleveland disappeared beneath 
the waves 
after all there was evidence that the lakes had been several 
feet higher some centuries earlier and there was speculation that 
that might have been the normal level 
some skeptics suggested that steps to lower the lakes might be 
risky and ineffective 
in the meantime the skeptics suggested wet weather might taper 
off and the problem could correct itself 
in the paper recently there have been stories that said in 
effect that the problem has corrected itself at least as far as 
lakes superior and michigan are concerned and the level has 
dropped so far that navigation in channels and harbors is posing 
some difficulties 
but for the moment we can be grateful that a couple of billion 
dollars wasnt spent on crash programs to eliminate one of those 
nonproblems 
