<TEXT>
this springs run of atlantic salmon 
in the connecticut river is less than onethird of last years the 
head of a joint federal and state program to restore the prize game 
fish said wednesday 
but biologists arent certain yet whether the cool spring 
weather has just slowed the fish or they died before reaching 
spawning age said stephen rideout executive director of the 
connecticut river atlantic salmon commission 
since the connecticut river tends to have the first run of the 
season along the east coast we wont have any reasonable 
assumptions until the end of the month but it appears that returns 
are also slow in the merrimack river and the rivers in maine 
rideout said normally the salmon run in the connecticut ends in 
midjuly 
so far this spring 81 returning salmon have been spotted in the 
connecticut river including 67 at the holyoke dam he said 
last year 294 fish had returned by early june he said and for 
the spring 353 salmon returned to the connecticut river 
this could be the first year since 1983 that we havent had an 
increase and thats a little dissappointing but you have to expect 
some ups and downs and as long as we can learn from what happend 
its not discouraging rideout said 
the first salmon returned to the river in the restoration 
program in 1975 before the first dams were built on the river in 
the 1700s biologists estimated that 40000 salmon migrated up the 
river annually 
rideout said commercial fishing off greenland and a disease that 
affected the fins of the young fish stocked in the lower reaches of 
the river in 1986 may have contributed to the lack of adult fish 
this spring salmon are hatched in fresh water migrate to the sea 
when they are about a year old and return to fresh water to spawn 
when they are about 3 years old 
young fish stocked in the upper tributaries of the river in 
vermont and new hampshire may also have had a high mortality rate 
because of low water when they were trying to make it downstream 
past hydropower dams to the sea in 1986 he said 
the river flow was at its lowest in 20 years in april and may 
of 1986 when they would have come downstream rideout said 
