soviet troops from afghanistan are being violated undermining 
confidence in other peace talks 
the soviet official did not identify the united states or 
pakistan as the offending parties but his implication was clear 
when one party observes its obligations under the geneva 
agreements while the other party is violating them this naturally 
causes us to have doubts about our partner and to refuse to trust 
him he said 
the united nations helped negotiate a pact signed in geneva 
which calls for the withdrawal of more than 100000 red army troops 
from afghanistan within a year and the repatriation of millions of 
afghan refugees who fled to pakistan and iran 
in his 45minute address shevardnadze called for reductions in 
conventional arms in europe including cutbacks by both sides of 
about 500000 soldiers each 
his speech included a call for a ban on space weapons a 
chemical weapons ban a un naval force and a central role for the 
united nations in verifying disarmament 
the soviet union announced a unilateral testing moratorium in 
august 1985 the united states refused to go along and the 
moratorium ended 1 years later 
the highlight of the speech appeared to be a renewal of the 
soviet offer 
our invariable position on a nuclear testing moratorium is 
still valid shevardnadze said on the basis of reciprocity 
with the united states we are ready to reintroduce and to observe 
it this time not for a year and a half but for all times 
without limiting and banning nuclear tests he said it is 
difficult or impossible to prevent the global spread of nuclear 
weapons 
the soviet foreign minister repeated his call for creation of 
un naval forces comprised of forces of the permanent members of 
the security council the soviet union the united states britain 
china and france 
on port calls shevardnadze said the soviet union was ready to 
announce the presence or absence of nuclear weapons aboard its 
naval ships calling at foreign ports 
the united states consistently has refused to make disclosures 
about port calls by nucleararmed ships 
