legislation approved by the house on wednesday 
would require telephones to be compatible with hearing aids 
the measure was passed 39115 a similar bill is pending in the 
senate 
the bill would require compatibility for all phones made in or 
imported into the united states one year after enactment of the 
measure mobile cellular and secure phones would be exempt 
cordless phones would be exempt for three years after enactment 
we simply cannot confine the hearing impaired to a world of 
silence said rep edward j markey dmass chairman of the 
house commerce and energy subcommittee on telecommunications 
more than half of the estimated 4 million hearingaid users in 
the united states use a hearing aid equipped with a telecoil 
which cuts the feedback a user would otherwise hear when talking on 
the telephone 
some hearing aidwearers pick up highpitched squeals when they 
use some noncompatible telephones especially those made abroad 
current law requires essential phones to be 
telecoilcompatible these include coinoperated phones and phones 
that are creditcard operated in places where no coin phone is 
nearby 
