resource as a personal gain its privatization 
landowners say its a way for farmers and ranchers to make some 
extra money and ease hunting pressure by controlling the number of 
hunters grosfield said it takes time to deal with each hunter who 
calls or knocks at the door 
a rancher is essentially subsidizing the recreating public 
to the extent of the time effort and expense it takes to 
accommodate that public theres something not equitable about 
that he said 
but its more than that 
its also kind of in response to what is seen as an overly 
aggressive attitude among some recreational groups to force issues 
like access especially with the stream access thing grosfield 
