arthur perdue never retired and he had a 
few words of advice on the subject for his son 
its like the throttle of an engine arthurs son frank 
perdue recalled as you get older you turn the throttle down a 
little bit 
frank perdue at 67 may be slowing down but its hard to tell 
although he recently stepped aside as chief executive officer of 
perdue farms inc the nations fourthlargest poultry producer 
hes still known nationwide as the tough guy who sells tender 
chickens 
its nothing like the end of an era said perdue who made 
himself and his poultry products famous through his television 
