<TEXT>
fear not all you who have botched a batch 
of laundry with an overdose of bleach now a little dash can 
breathe new life into your wardrobe 
a texas clothing company is marketing a line of apparel that can 
change color with controlled amounts of liquid bleach and cold 
water 
that might not sound so new after all just about any fabric 
will fade when it is bleached but with the colormagic process 
cloth changes from teal blue to peach from royal blue to hot pink 
or from violet to orange among other combinations 
i think the possibilities are unlimited said tom ahmann 
executive vice president of el pasobased greater texas finishing 
corp which dyes and markets the line of clothes its so 
different from whats been offered before 
if colormagic takes off it would mark the second time that 
greater texas caught the beginning of a clothing fad the 
corporation was one of the first to offer acidwashing for 
companies that make denim clothing 
the colormagic process was invented by owen sercus a textile 
chemist at the fashion institute of technology in new york and 
greater texas is the sole manufacturer 
there are two basic ways to change the color of the garments 
first the color of the entire garment can be changed by tossing it 
in a coldwater wash cycle with a specific amount of liquid bleach 
colors usually can be changed twice for example from hot pink to 
apricot to cantaloupe 
the colorchanging can even be done in the same wash with other 
clothes because the dye dissolves and is not absorbed by other 
clothes in the washer greater texas officials say 
the garments which now are made only in girls and junior 
sizes also can become canvases for people who want to personalize 
their own clothes in a process that could be likened to reverse 
tiedyeing people can use paint brushes or cotton swabs to brush 
or draw designs onto the fabric with diluted liquid bleach 
after the designs are drawn the garment is dried thoroughly 
then washed in cold water to remove the bleach the designs are the 
color of the underlying fabric 
ahmann said wednesday he thinks the clothes will be a hit 
because consumers are looking for more and more individuality in 
their clothes with something like this they can get it 
the colormagic line consists of jean jackets hats socks 
jeans tshirts belts walking shorts and camp shirts and is 
available at five stores nationwide bloomingdales in new york 
marshallfields in chicago macys in san francisco highbees in 
cleveland and the popular in el paso 
ahmann said the line will be expanded later to adult sizes and 
might be offered in more stores once manufacturing capacity 
increases the clothes are not cheap jeans cost 48 tshirts are 
19 and socks are 10 a pair 
