<TEXT>
an inexpensive voiceactivated device to enable 
the severely handicapped to control their home environments was 
unveiled wednesday by quartet technology inc 
the simplicity series 5 a voicecomputer device was introduced 
at a news conference by the tyngsboro massbased company 
the series 5 is a simple almost flat device that looks like a 
humidifier with just a few key words the machine can perform a 
number of tasks including turning lights off and on and turning 
appliances on dialing the phone and answering the phone 
the device can also control television sets and electric beds 
and be used in conjunction with accessories like page turners and 
drapery and door openers 
michael rourke a spokesman for quartet said the device is not 
the first voiceactivated machine to help the severely disabled but 
is by far the simplest and least expensive on the market 
when available in the next month or so the series 5 will retail 
for 2490 quartet officials claim that similar devices on the 
market sell for about 12000 
sue haider 41 who is now quadriplegic after a shooting 
accident in february has worked with the device for the last two 
months she said using it in her home will mean greatly increased 
independence and less need for aroundtheclock attendants 
i love it i really do said haider you get a sense of 
someone being there with you it means i wont need 24hour 
attendants 
</TEXT>
