murray ohio manufacturing co is 
discussing the possibility of selling the company to parties other 
than ab electrolux of sweden which has offered to buy it 
president john l duncan said wednesday 
the option is one of many being discussed by murray ohio in 
light of the swedish appliance manufacturers unsolicited 197 
million offer for murray ohio duncan said 
on tuesday murray ohio said its directors rejected as 
inadequate a 52ashare tender offer from ab electrolux and 
recommended that the companys shareholders refrain from tendering 
their shares 
the board has authorized us to explore a lot of options other 
than electroluxs offer duncan said wednesday 
we are talking to third parties about buying murray ohio and 
other options including a recapitalization he said 
but duncan said the discussions do not mean that a decision has 
been made to sell the brentwoodbased company which makes lawn 
mowers and bicycles at a plant in lawrenceburg he gave no details 
of the discussions 
the swedish company said it was disappointed with the boards 
decision but said it would pursue its offer which was launched 
may 24 
in trading on the new york stock exchange murray ohio rose 
137 a share to 6387 on wednesday 
ab electrolux is not connected to electrolux inc of marietta 
ga which makes vacuum cleaners 
